    "narrative": "The LawDog lineup is primed for an offensive surge today, anchored by a trio of high-efficiency plays. **Daulton Varsho** (72.16) and **Lawrence Butler** (72.16) share the top spot on our board; **Daulton Varsho** benefits from a strong SP matchup against Woods Richardson (4.47 xERA) and an optimal #2 spot in the order, while **Lawrence Butler** carries the momentum of a leadoff assignment against Holmes, where his dynamic platoon advantage (+13%) makes him a foundational play. Close behind, **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** (71.61) remains our most reliable anchor against Elder. We are also looking for significant upside from **Matt Chapman** (70.11), who is exploiting a +16% park factor in his matchup against Baz. The park factor is a recurring theme today; **Luis Arraez**, **Taylor Ward**, and **Jung Hoo Lee** all see their daily scores bolstered by playing conditions that favor hitters, with **Taylor Ward** specifically primed to produce despite a slight platoon drag.\n\nOur most difficult decision centered on the utility slot, where **Brendan Donovan** (59.16) fell just short of the cut. While **Brendan Donovan** benefits from a robust +14% dynamic platoon edge, the optimizer favored **Jeremiah Jackson** (59.51) and our starters due to the superior base production of our core infielders. Notably, the potential for high-speed utility plays remains a priority; **Tyler Freeman** (69.05) earns a strong start today precisely because he draws a favorable matchup against Walker Buehler and possesses a 90% SB efficiency rating against a slower delivery, fitting our mandate to aggressively pursue stolen bases. \n\nRisk management remains a priority given that several hitters, including **Cal Raleigh**, **Will Smith**, and **Tyler Freeman**, are currently operating with \"Lineup Pending\" tags. While we have projected them into the heart of their respective orders, any late lineup shifts could necessitate a swap for **Brendan Donovan** or **Gavin Sheets**, both of whom are ready to slot in should an opportunity arise. Furthermore, while we are avoiding the truly elite arms today, **Bryson Stott** faces a moderate hurdle in Soroka; we are counting on his +13% platoon edge to maintain his efficiency floor. We will continue to monitor the weather and official lineups closely to protect our game caps.",
